# Product Vision Narrative

A framework for communicating a compelling product vision that aligns teams and inspires execution.

Great products are built around a clear narrative.

---

# Purpose

The Product Vision Narrative helps product leaders:

• communicate the future of the product  
• align teams around a shared direction  
• create clarity for stakeholders  

---

# Structure of a Product Vision Narrative

The World Today
↓
The Problem
↓
The Opportunity
↓
The Product Vision
↓
The Future State

---

# 1. The World Today

Describe the current state of the world.

Example:

Users struggle with fragmented workflows, limited access to information, and tools that fail to adapt to their needs.

---

# 2. The Problem

Explain the key challenges users face.

Example:

Athletes recovering from injuries often lack structured guidance and consistent recovery plans.

---

# 3. The Opportunity

Explain why now is the right time to solve the problem.

Drivers may include:

• technology shifts  
• AI capabilities  
• new user behaviors  

---

# 4. The Product Vision

Describe the product's future impact.

Example:

A platform that intelligently guides athletes through recovery, adapting programs based on progress and performance.

---

# 5. The Future State

Paint a picture of what success looks like.

Example:

Athletes recover faster, avoid reinjury, and maintain peak performance through personalized recovery systems.

